{
  "text": "Our study provides morphological evidence for the occurrence of natural hybridization between the Culex pipiens complex forms pallens and molestus in Northwestern Kyushu, Japan. Morphologically intermediate individuals that were observed were suggested to be hybrids of the two forms. This hypothesis was confirmed by the PCR results. Hybrids between forms pallens and molestus have been detected in Tokyo, Japan, as determined by PCR-based identification, but without morphological studies [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
